      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Mixing ibuprofen and codeine is dangerous because codeine affects your breathing directly, and combining it with other painkillers can push you into an overdose without any prior warning signs or tolerance. Appendicitis can present with wavy pain before becoming constant, so assuming it's just cramps is risky and could lead to a ruptured appendix if you don't get it checked immediately. Please go to the emergency room now instead of trying to sleep it off; delaying treatment for appendicitis can be life-threatening and is far more dangerous than the cost or wait time of an ER visit.",
